            <p:rationale>By keeping data stateless, state does not need to be tracked and replicated between agencies, making systems much more scalable.</p:rationale>
            <p:implications>If it is expected that many messages per second will be exchanged, then the integration infrastructure must provide stateless data. This means no resources (memory, process) must be retained for a message that is sent, and that there is no waiting for a response; this is treated as a new message. Also, process logic is not housed in the integration infrastructure because it is full of State.</p:implications>
